Time Complexity:

Let n = size of array

    Counting occurrences → O(n)
    Overwriting array → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Only constant variables used (count0, count1)

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Initialize counters:
   - count0 = number of 0’s
   - count1 = number of 1’s

2. Traverse array:
   - Count occurrences of 0 and 1
   - Remaining elements are 2’s

3. Overwrite array:

   - Fill first count0 positions with 0
   - Fill next count1 positions with 1
   - Fill remaining positions with 2

4. Return sorted array (in-place)






class Solution {
    public void sortColors(int[] nums) {
        int count0=0;
        int count1=0;
        for(int ele: nums){
            if(ele==0) count0++;
            if(ele==1) count1++;
        }
        int i=0;
        while(i<nums.length && count0!=0){
            nums[i]=0;
            count0--;
            i++;
        }
        while(i<nums.length && count1!=0){
            nums[i]=1;
            count1--;
            i++;
        }
        while(i<nums.length){
            nums[i]=2;
            i++;
        }
    }
}
